public interface InformationalBOM
extends BusinessObjectModule

Business object types that do require to display business object information will require bespoke implementations of this BusinessObjectModule (BOM).

On adding business objects to the change set, infrastructure requires the details of the available business objects for a business object type to display the business objects and their related information for a change set. Also,the home page details of a business object (if exists), are required by the infrastructure to display the home page of the business object.

Infrastructure depends on BusinessObjectModule implementation for every business object type to determine business object details.

Infrastructure delegates the responsibility to individual Business Object Module(BOM) implementation to determine the details required to display the business objects.

It is now possible to specify static information on InformationalBOM implementation through BOTraits annotation. The desired business functionality that is applicable based on the properties exposed by a business object type will be decided by the infrastructure. Refer BOTraits for more details on this usage.

getAllBusinessObjectInformation

java.util.List<BusinessObjectInformation> getAllBusinessObjectInformation()
                                                                          throws AppException,
                                                                                 InformationalException
Gets the list of all the available business objects for the given business object type. Each entry in the list contains localisable name for the instance, the details for the instance(if any), and the business object identifier for the instance. The localisable name and details are required by the infrastructure to render on the screen. The Business Object Identifier is required by the infrastructure in order to add the selected Business Object(s) to the Change Set.

Returns:
List of business object information instances BusinessObjectInformation
Throws:
AppException - Generic Exception Signature.
InformationalException - Generic Exception Signature.
